@node "Installation" "Installation"


@{i}@{u}@{fg shadow}Installation@{ui}@{uu}@{fg text}



   All you have to do to install this program is copy it into what ever
directory you want and it will run from there.

It reqiures gadtools.library version 37+ to run so you need kickstart 2+ and
thats it!


                                                         @{"BackĀToĀMain." link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"


@{i}@{u}Usage@{ui}@{uu}


The program currently supports the following arguments from shell,

X,/N,Y/N,PRIORITY=PRI/N

X --- X is the X position on the frontmost public screen. Y --- Y is the Y
position on the frontmost public screen. PRI - PRI is the priority you want
the program to run at.

To quit all you have to do is select the window and click on the right mouse
button.

The arguments will be alterable through tool types as soon as I workout how to
get the program to read them :-)

The Program will run for about ten minutes then will quit this is just to
encorage you to @{"REGISTER." link "Register" 0}

                                                           @{"BackĀToĀMain." link "Main" 0}
@endnode

